		<td><b>&quot;Courage&quot; PC-Engine diskmag</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Since no one else has mentioned it here, I will. Chris Covell has released a small diskmag for the PC-Engine / TurboGrafx, which features a couple of articles / charts, as well as SID emulation for its background music.<br /><br />The ROM can be found <a href="http://www.chrismcovell.com/data/CMC_Courage_Diskmag.zip" class="postlink">here</a><br /><br />And <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vof2Z8Vf3bk" class="postlink">here's</a> a video I captured from my TG16. The music sounds wrong on a 50 Hz console though, since it apparently uses the vblank interrupt to time the music playback and expects interrupts at 60 Hz. If you want to hear what it really sounds like and read the full articles you should run it on a PC-Engine or NTSC TurboGrafx, or in an emulator like Mednafen.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


